  "text": "To explore the seasonal variations and inter-annual trend of the archetypes, we defined the matrix A of mixture coefficients rather than B as the temporal variability of archetypal patterns of the seasonal precipitation [CITATION_1] . Although the matrix B also contains the time series of length n, it describes which day is characterized best by one particular pure archetypal pattern. Thus, the time series of the k-th column of B may miss the day when an archetype is active if another archetype is also active, and does not represent how dominant each archetype is in any given days.",
